<title>UK: REED DIVES AFTER RESULTS DISAPPOINT.</title>
<headline>REED DIVES AFTER RESULTS DISAPPOINT.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-08-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Anglo-Dutch publisher Reed Elsevier fell 26-1/2p to 603-1/2p in early trade after first half results disappointed top market expectations.</p>
<p>The company said first half pre-tax profits came to 419 million stg, up very slightly from 416 million the previous year. A dividend of 4.4 pence a share was slightly below expectations.</p>
<p>Analysts expected profits between 411 million and 445 million and a dividend of 4.5p.</p>
